  { q: 'Does the Sennheiser Momentum 4 have good noise cancellation?', a: 'Yes, but it is not the best in class. The adaptive ANC does an excellent job with mid-to-high frequency noise (voices, keyboard clatter, office chatter) and a good job with steady mid-frequency sounds (airplane cabin). Where it falls short is low-frequency rumble — the Sony XM5 blocks more of the deep engine drone you hear on planes and trains. If ANC is your top priority, the Sony XM5 wins. If sound quality and battery are your priorities, the Momentum 4 wins.' },
